2 Technical requirements

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373833970_87496_14528

2

Technical requirements

2.1 Structure

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_831523_16027

2.1

Structure

2.1.1 Head

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947269_619833_17513

2.1.1

Head

The Mars Rover shall have a head

2.1.1.1 Head Position

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710152799440_775076_5744

2.1.1.1

Head Position

The Head of the Mars Rover shall be higher mounted than body, suspension and traction unit.

2.1.1.2 Head Function

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153330085_930613_5754

2.1.1.2

Head Function

The Head of the Mars Rover shall carry sensors and a LED Display.

2.1.2 Body

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710146462874_714909_5562

2.1.2

Body

The Mars Rover shall have a body

2.1.3 Suspension

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710146492047_939247_5565

2.1.3

Suspension

The Mars Rover shall have a suspension suspending the traction unit

2.1.4 Traction Unit

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710146526694_117941_5568

2.1.4

Traction Unit

The Mars Rover shall have a traction unit providing traction to the ground

2.2 Power Supply

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_990229_16028

2.2

Power Supply

The Mars Rover shall have a power supply.

2.2.1 External Power Supply

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947269_334692_17515

2.2.1

External Power Supply

The Mars Rover shall be operable with internal power supply only.

2.2.2 Internal Power Supply

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947269_839759_17516

2.2.2

Internal Power Supply

The Mars Rover shall have a power supply fulfilling all of the following conditions:* it contains an energy storage system* it contains an energy management system* it contains a power distribution system

2.2.2.1 Energy Storage

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373992768_924005_18953

2.2.2.1

Energy Storage

The Mars Rover shall have means to re-charde its energy storage system.

2.2.2.2 Available Power

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373992768_101922_18958

2.2.2.2

Available Power

The Mars Rover shall be operable for 4h under all of the following conditions:* The energy storage is fully loaded at the beginning* The operation requires less than or equal to 60% of the max energy in peak load* the environmental conditions are mission normal

2.2.3 Energy Re-Charging

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947269_80329_17517

2.2.3

Energy Re-Charging

The Mars Rover shall re-charge the energy storage from 10% to 80% in 4h under the following conditions:* re-charging at mission normal conditions* no energy consumption of the Mars Rover since the re-charging period

2.2.5 Electrical Values

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373886850_739640_15912

2.2.5

Electrical Values

The Mars Rover shall use 12 V DC voltage

2.2.5.1 Motor Voltage

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1555340930579_881851_34234

2.2.5.1

Motor Voltage

The Mars Rover shall have one main drive motor for each traction device fulfilling the following conditions:* using 12 V voltage* using not more than 30 A current

2.2.5.2 Encoder Voltage

_2022x_8a9027b_1707924576905_883240_5487

2.2.5.2

Encoder Voltage

The Mars Rover shall have an encoder powered by 5 V voltage.

2.2.4 Energy Management

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373886850_551019_15911

2.2.4

Energy Management

The Mars Rover shall have an energy management fullfilling all of the following conditions:* distributing the energy to all systems* prioritizing the energy available for the different systems* limiting energy to individual systems to prioritize individual systems* managing energy that the Mars Rover can recharge by itself in a time period of less than 24 hours

2.3 Motion

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_489031_16029

2.3

Motion

The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself.

2.3.2 Motion over Obstacles

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947238_635549_17411

2.3.2

Motion over Obstacles

The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself over obstacles which fullfill one of the following condition:* the obstacle is max. 20 cm high* the slope angle uphil is max. 30 degree* the slope angle downhil is max. 30 degree* the roll angle of the Mars Rover since moving over the obstacle never exceeds an angle of 30 degree

2.3.2.1 Deformation of the bogie

_2022x_8a9027b_1708424764583_139395_5943

2.3.2.1

Deformation of the bogie

The bogie of the suspension system shall not bend more than 5% since all motion events.

2.3.2.2 Plastic deformation of the bogie

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710147594026_511625_5572

2.3.2.2

Plastic deformation of the bogie

The bogie of the suspension system shall not deform plastically for bending less than or equal to 7%.

2.3.4 Motion Ground Contact

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947238_606232_17414

2.3.4

Motion Ground Contact

The Mars Rover shall produce a ground pressure of max. 20 kPa.

2.3.1 Max Motion Speed

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947253_22759_17417

2.3.1

Max Motion Speed

The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself with a max. speed of 7 m/s.

2.3.3 Motion over slopes

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373947253_787088_17420

2.3.3

Motion over slopes

The Mars Rover shall be able to move on slopes which fullfill the following condition:* slope angle uphill max. 20 degree* slope angle downhill max. 30 degree* slope angle sidehill max 15 degree

2.3.5 Electric Motion Drive

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888774_76355_15935

2.3.5

Electric Motion Drive

The Mars Rover shall have one left and one right traction device both driven by one electrical motor each.

2.3.8 Motion Distance

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888774_384276_15938

2.3.8

Motion Distance

The Mars Rover shall be able to move at least 100m per day on all slopes where it is able to move on.

2.3.7 Min Motion Speed

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888774_923366_15937

2.3.7

Min Motion Speed

The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself with a min. speed of 1 m/min

2.3.6 Start Driving

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888774_941195_15936

2.3.6

Start Driving

The Mars Rover shall start driving by itself on all slopes where it is able to move on.

2.3.9 Stopping

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1555336591336_85392_31015

2.3.9

Stopping

The Mars Rover shall be able to stop moving by itself down to 0 m/s speed.

2.3.10 Hill Holding

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148366772_438416_5581

2.3.10

Hill Holding

The Mars Rover shall maintain 0 m/s motion on all slopes it is able to move on.

2.3.11 Steering

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148561688_473742_5584

2.3.11

Steering

The Mars Rover shall be able to change driving direction to the left and to the right.

2.3.12 Diving Direction

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148601847_750005_5587

2.3.12

Diving Direction

The Mars Rover shall be able to drive forwards and backwards.

2.3.13 Navigate

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148650016_796202_5590

2.3.13

Navigate

The Mars Rover shall be able to calculate a route between its actual position and a target position

2.3.13.1 Detecting Obstacles

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148712446_394547_5593

2.3.13.1

Detecting Obstacles

The Mars Rover shall be able to identify obstacles by itself

2.3.13.2 Map Data

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148782585_264451_5596

2.3.13.2

Map Data

The Mars Rover shall have map data stored enabling it to calculate a route between its actual position and a target position

2.3.13.3 Preventing Obstacles

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710148844988_144183_5599

2.3.13.3

Preventing Obstacles

The Mars Rover shall prevent driving over obstacles if all of the following conditions are true:* the obstacle exceeds the measures of an acceptable obstacle as required in 1.1.3.2* a rout is available around the obstacle or rearwards to a position capable to reach the target without crossing the obstacle.

2.4 Remote Control

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_844710_16030

2.4

Remote Control

The Mars Rover shall be controllable remote.

2.4.2 Remote Steering

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888790_510287_15941

2.4.2

Remote Steering

The Mars Rover steering direction shall be controllable remote.

2.4.1 Remote Speed Control

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373888774_288492_15940

2.4.1

Remote Speed Control

The Mars Rover speed shall be controllable remote.

2.4.3 Remote Control Priority

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710149292477_668117_5602

2.4.3

Remote Control Priority

The Mars Rover remote control shall be able to overrule the auto navigation function.

2.5 Optical Feedback

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_183392_16031

2.5

Optical Feedback

The Mars Rover shall provide optical information if it is operable or not.

2.5.1 LED

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373890795_302548_15964

2.5.1

LED

The Mars Rover shall have a LED for optical information if it is operable or not.

2.6 Max Mass

_17_0_3_1_60c0217_1554373894872_124599_16032

2.6

Max Mass

The Mars Rover shall have a total mass of not more than 12 kg

2.6.1 Mars Rover Mass

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153834097_967050_5805

2.6.1

Mars Rover Mass

The Mars Rover shall have a total mass of not more than 10 kg

2.6.2 Payload

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153885017_514661_5808

2.6.2

Payload

The Mars Rover shall have a payload of 2 kg.

2.7 Mars Rover Capabilities

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710152920321_382759_5749

2.7

Mars Rover Capabilities

The Mars Rover shall be able to execute the following operations individually and not in combination:* Moving on Mars surface* Capturing optical information* Capturing video information* Capturing audio information* Sampling of Probes of solid material of individual diameter not bigger than 20 mm* Sampling of probes of fluid material in the range of ph-value 0 to 11* Sampling of probes of gas of not more than 50 mm³ volume and pressure between 1 hPa up to 3.000 hPa* Sampling of biological probes of not more than 50 mm³ volume and not more than 30 mm length in any direction

2.7.1 Mars Rover Communication

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153615080_304380_5787

2.7.1

Mars Rover Communication

The Mars Rover shall be able to communicate sampled information to the Mars station.

2.7.2 Information Storage

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153678770_496381_5792

2.7.2

Information Storage

The Mars Rover shall be capable to store information up to 2 TB

2.7.3 Sample Storage

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153727491_409919_5797

2.7.3

Sample Storage

The Mars Rover shall be able to store probes up to 48 h long.

2.7.4 Unloading

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710153776399_96192_5800

2.7.4

Unloading

The Mars Rover shall be able to unload stored probes into the Mars Station.

2.9 Operating on Mars

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710151635216_154098_5695

2.9

Operating on Mars

The Mars Rover shall be able to operate on the planet Mars.

2.9.1 Operating Atmosphere

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710151675649_994932_5700

2.9.1

Operating Atmosphere

The Mars Rover shall be able to operate in Mars atmosphere for at least 25 years.

2.9.2 Mars Gravity

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710151718558_644987_5705

2.9.2

Mars Gravity

The Mars Rover shall be able to operate under Mars gravity of 3.71 m/s².

2.9.3 Mars Temperatures

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710151896250_201297_5710

2.9.3

Mars Temperatures

The Mars Rover shall be able to operate in a temperature range from -80°C up to 80°C

2.9.4 Mars Radiation

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710152037892_253674_5713

2.9.4

Mars Radiation

The Mars Rover shall be able to be fully operable under constant cosmic radiation of at least 250 mSv.

2.8 Landing on Mars

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710150433825_282917_5653

2.8

Landing on Mars

The Mars Rover shall be able to land on planet Mars.

2.8.1 Landing Temperatures

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710150476050_13127_5658

2.8.1

Landing Temperatures

The Mars Rover shall resist temperatures of not more than 100°C for not more than 7 minutes while staying full functional.

2.8.2 Landing Deceleration

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710150561344_954069_5661

2.8.2

Landing Deceleration

The Mars Rover shall be able to withstand landing deceleration as listed below:* Deceleration from 20.000 km/h at Mars atmosphere entry to 1.500 km/h in 4 minutes.* Deceleration from 1.500 km/s to 25 m/s in 3 minutes

2.8.3 Landing speed

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710150880576_958104_5666

2.8.3

Landing speed

The Mars Rover shall be full operable after a landing on Mars with the following conditions beeing true:* The vertical speed at ground contact is not higher than 1 m/s* The horizontal speed at graund contact is not higher than 1 m/s

2.8.4 Landing Orientation

_2021x_2_8d501e7_1710151377993_602525_5676

2.8.4

Landing Orientation

The Mars Rover shall land on Mars with the traction units first contacting the ground.
